@page "/"

<h3>Field-Level Async Validation — Blazor Web App</h3>
<p>
    This app is organized around the four API proposal scenarios. Each scenario page uses the
    same Blazor pattern: <code>&lt;DataAnnotationsValidator /&gt;</code>, <code>OnSubmit</code>, and
    <code>await _editContext.ValidateAsync()</code>. Pages with async property attributes also show
    <code>IsValidationPending()</code> spinners while those checks are in flight.
</p>

<div class="alert alert-primary">
    <strong>Key idea:</strong> <code>DataAnnotationsValidator</code> now handles async validation
    directly. Field changes can run async property validators, and submit can run full-model async
    validation without the manual plumbing older samples needed.
</div>

<div class="list-group">
    <a href="/scenario1" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 1:</strong> <code>User</code> — no interface, sync <code>[IsValidName]</code>
        plus async <code>[UsernameAvailableAsync]</code>
    </a>
    <a href="/scenario2" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 2:</strong> <code>Order</code> — <code>IValidatableObject</code> with async
        <code>[AsyncProductExists]</code> on <code>ProductName</code> and full-model submit validation
    </a>
    <a href="/scenario3" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 3:</strong> <code>MoneyTransfer</code> —
        <code>IAsyncValidatableObject</code>; no async property attributes, async work happens on
